(a) beginning in the second quarter of 2004,
the company developed a methodology to allocate net investment income and
invested assets to the identified segments. see note 2 to the consolidated
financial statements for further discussion of this methodology.
(b) expense allocations are determined in
accordance with prescribed statutory accounting practices. these practices make
a reasonable allocation of all expenses to those product lines with which they
are associated.
